obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (31763)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00022_192307_1523344595133&sectionId=31763&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00022_192307_1523344595133
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Indian Naval`
  line `Armament Act, 1923.`
  line
  line `^1[(2) It extends to the whole of India except ^2[the territories which, immediately before the 1st`
  line `November, 1956, were comprised in Part B States].]`
  line
  line `(3) It shall come into force on such date^3 as the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette appoint.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1950, for sub-section (2).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by the Adaptation of Laws (No. 3) Order, 1956, for "Part B States".`
  line
  line `3. This Act was brought into force on the 10th November, 1923, see Gazette of India, 1923, Pt. I, p. 617.`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (31764)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00022_192307_1523344595133&sectionId=31764&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00022_192307_1523344595133
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act unless there is anything repugnant in the subject or context,--`
  line
  line `(a) "competent Court" means the High Court or such other Court having unlimited original`
  line `civil jurisdiction as the Central Government may declare to be a competent Court for the purposes`
  line `of this Act;`
  line
  line `(b) "ship" means any boat, vessel, battery or craft, whether wholly or partly constructed, which`
  line `is intended to float or is capable of floating, on water, and includes all equipment belonging to any`
  line ship;
  line
  line `^1[(bb) "States" denotes all the territories ^2[to which this Act extends]; and`
  line
  line `^3[(c) "the Treaty" means the Treaty for the Limitation of Naval Armament and for the`
  line `Exchange of Information concerning Naval Construction signed in London on behalf of His`
  line `Majesty on the twenty-fifth day of March, 1936.]`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by the A. O. 1950.`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by the Adaptation of Laws (No. 3) Order, 1956, for "for the time being comprised within Part A States and Part C`
  line `States".`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 2 of 1937, s. 3, for clause (c).`
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (31765)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Restriction on building or equipping vessels of war.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00022_192307_1523344595133&sectionId=31765&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00022_192307_1523344595133
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `No person shall, except under and in`
  line `accordance with the conditions of a licence granted under this Act,--`
  line
  line `(a) build any vessel of war, or alter, arm or equip any ship so as to adapt her for use as a vessel`
  line `of war; or`
  line
  line `(b) despatch or deliver, or allow to be despatched or delivered, from any place in the States any`
  line `ship which has been, either wholly or partly, built, altered, armed or equipped as a vessel of war in`
  line `any part of His Majesty's Dominions or^9[of India] otherwise than under and in accordance with`
  line `any law for the time being in force in that part ^10***.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1950, for "in a State in India".`
  line
  line `2. The words "or State" omitted, ibid.`
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (31766)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title Licences.
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00022_192307_1523344595133&sectionId=31766&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00022_192307_1523344595133
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) A licence under this Act for any of the purposes specified in section 3 may be`
  line `granted by the ^1[Central Government], and shall not be refused unless it appears to the ^1[Central`
  line `Government] that such refusal is necessary for the purpose of securing the observance of the`
  line `obligations imposed by the Treaty; and, where a licence is granted subject to conditions, the`
  line `conditions shall be such only as the ^1[Central Government] may think necessary for the purpose`
  line aforesaid.
  line
  line `(2) An application for a licence under this section shall be in such form and shall be accompanied`
  line `by such designs and particulars as the ^1[Central Government] may, by general or special order,`
  line require.
  line
  line `^2[(3) Any person who, in pursuance of a licence granted under sub-section (1) before the`
  line `commencement of the Indian Naval Armament (Amendment) Act, 1937 (2 of 1937), is engaged in`
  line `building any vessel of war or in altering, arming or equipping any ship so as to adapt her for use as a`
  line `vessel of war, or is about to despatch or deliver, or allow to be despatched or delivered, from any`
  line `place within the States any ship which has been so built, altered, armed or equipped, either entirely or`
  line `partly within the States, shall, upon written demand, furnish to the ^1]1[Central Government] such`
  line `designs and particulars as may be required by the^1[Central Government] for the purpose of securing`
  line `the observance of the obligations imposed by the Treaty.]`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1937, for "L.G."`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 2 of 1937, s. 4.`
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (31767)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title Offences.
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00022_192307_1523344595133&sectionId=31767&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00022_192307_1523344595133
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any person contravenes any of the provisions of section 3`
  line `^1[or fails to comply with the provisions of sub-section (3) of section 4]; he shall be punishable with`
  line `imprisonment for a term which may extend to two years, or with fine which may extend to one`
  line `thousand rupees, or with both.`
  line
  line `(2) Where an offence punishable under sub-section (1) has been committed by a`
  line `company or corporation, every director and manager of such company or corporation shall be`
  line `punishable thereunder unless he proves that the act constituting the offence took place without his`
  line `knowledge and consent.`
  line
  line `(3) Nothing contained in section 517 or section 518 or section 520 of the Code of Criminal`
  line `Procedure, 1898 (5 of 1898)^2`
  line `, shall be deemed to authorise the destruction or confiscation under the`
  line `order of any criminal court of any ship which is liable to forfeiture under this Act or of any part of`
  line `such ship.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 2 of 1937, s. 4.`
  line
  line `2. See now of the-Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974).`
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (31768)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title Liability.
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00022_192307_1523344595133&sectionId=31768&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00022_192307_1523344595133
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `Any ship which has been, either wholly or partly, built,`
  line `altered, armed or equipped as a vessel of war in the States in contravention of section 3, or in any ^1***`
  line `part of His Majesty's Dominions or ^2[of India] in contravention of any like provision of law in force`
  line `in that part ^3*** , shall, if found in the States, be liable to forfeiture under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The word "other" omitted by the A.O. 1950.`
  line
  line `2. Subs., ibid., for "any State in India".`
  line
  line `3. The words "or State" omitted, ibid.`
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (31769)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Seizure, detention and search of ships.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00022_192307_1523344595133&sectionId=31769&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00022_192307_1523344595133
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where a ship is liable to forfeiture under this`
  line Act,--
  line
  line `(a) any Presidency Magistrate or Magistrate of the first class, or`
  line
  line `(a) any commissioned officer on full pay in the ^1[Armed Forces of the Union], ^2*** or`
  line
  line `(b) any officer of customs or police officer not below such rank^3 as may be designated in this`
  line `behalf by the Central Government,`
  line
  line `may seize such ship and detain it, and, if the ship is found at sea within the territorial waters of the`
  line `States, may bring it to any convenient port in the States.`
  line
  line `(2) Any officer taking any action under sub-section (1) shall forthwith report the same through his`
  line `official superiors to the ^4[Central Government].`
  line
  line `(3) The ^4[Central Government] shall, within thirty days of the seizure, either cause the ship to be`
  line `released or make or cause to be made, in the manner hereinafter provided, an application for the`
  line `forfeiture thereof, and may make such orders for the temporary disposal of the ship as it thinks`
  line suitable.
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1950, for "military, naval or air service of His Majesty".`
  line
  line `2. The words "or any Gazetted Officer of the Royal Indian Marine Service" rep. by the A.O. 1937.`
  line
  line `3. See Gazette of India, 1924. Pt. I, p. 188.`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by the A.O. 1937, for "L.G.".`
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (31770)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Procedure in forfeiture of ships.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1937, for "L.G.".`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00022_192307_1523344595133&sectionId=31770&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00022_192307_1523344595133
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `(1) An application for the forfeiture of a ship under this Act`
  line `may be made by, or under authority from, the ^1[Central Government] to any competent Court within`
  line `the local limits of whose jurisdiction the ship is for the time being.`
  line
  line `(2) On receipt of any such application, the Court shall cause notice thereof and of the date fixed for`
  line `the hearing of the application to be served upon all persons appearing to it to have an interest in the`
  line `ship, and may give such directions for the temporary disposal of the ship as it thinks fit.`
  line
  line `(3) For the purpose of disposing of an application under this section, the Court shall have the same`
  line `powers and follow, as nearly as may be, the same procedure as it respectively has and follows for the`
  line `purpose of the trial of suits under the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908), and any order made`
  line `by the Court under this section shall be deemed to be a decree, and the provisions of the said Code in`
  line `regard to the execution of decrees shall, as far as they are applicable, apply accordingly.`
  line
  line `(4) Where the Court is satisfied that the ship is liable to forfeiture under this Act, it shall pass an`
  line `order forfeiting the ship to Government:`
  line
  line `Provided that, where any person having an interest in the ship proves to the satisfaction of the`
  line `Court that he has not abetted, or connived at, or by his negligence facilitated, in any way, a`
  line `contravention of section 3 in respect of the ship, and such ship has not been built as a vessel of war, it`
  line `may pass such other order as it thinks fit in respect of the ship or, if it be sold, of the sale proceeds`
  line `thereof:`
  line
  line `Provided further that in no case shall any ship which has been altered, armed or equipped as a`
  line `vessel of war be released until it has been restored, to the satisfaction of the ^1[Central Government], to`
  line `such condition as not to render it liable to forfeiture under this Act.`
  line
  line `(5) The ^1[Central Government] or any person aggrieved by any order of a Court, other than a High`
  line `Court, under this section may, within three months of the date of such order, appeal to the High Court.`
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (31771)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Disposal of forfeit.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00022_192307_1523344595133&sectionId=31771&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00022_192307_1523344595133
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `Where a ship has been forfeited to Government under section 8, it may be`
  line `disposed of in such manner as the ^1[Central Government] ^2*** directs:`
  line
  line `Provided that, where the ship is sold under this section, due regard shall be had to the obligations`
  line `imposed by the Treaty.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1937, for "L.G."`
  line
  line `2. The words "subject to the control of the G.G. in C." rep by the A.O. 1937.`
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (31772)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Special proof of relevant facts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00022_192307_1523344595133&sectionId=31772&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00022_192307_1523344595133
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `If, in any trial, appeal or other proceeding under the`
  line `foregoing provisions of this Act, any question arises as to whether a ship is a vessel of war or whether`
  line `any alteration, arming or equipping of a ship is such as to adapt it for use as a vessel of war, the`
  line `question shall be referred to and determined by the Central Government, whose decision shall be final`
  line `and shall not be questioned in any court.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (31773)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Penalties for proceeding to sea after seizure.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes `1. See now the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00022_192307_1523344595133&sectionId=31773&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00022_192307_1523344595133
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where a ship which has been seized or`
  line `detained under section 7 or section 8 and has not been released by competent authority under this Act`
  line `proceeds to sea, the master of the ship shall be punishable with fine which may extend to one`
  line `thousand rupees, and the owner and any person who sends the ship to sea shall be likewise so`
  line `punishable unless such owner or person proves that the offence was committed without his knowledge`
  line `and consent.`
  line
  line `(2) Where any ship so proceeding to sea takes to sea, when on board thereof in the execution of his`
  line `duty, any officer empowered by this Act to seize and detain the ship, the owner and master shall`
  line `further each be liable, on the order of the Court trying an offence punishable under sub-section (1), to`
  line `pay all the expenses of and incidental to such officer being taken to sea, and shall further be`
  line `punishable with fine which may extend to one hundred rupees for every day until such officer returns`
  line `or until such time as would enable him after leaving the ship to return to the port from which he was`
  line taken.
  line
  line `(3) Any expenses ordered to be paid under sub-section (2) may be recovered in the manner`
  line `provided in the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1898 (5 of 1898)^1 for the recovery of a fine.`
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (31774)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Power to enter dock-yards, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes `1. See now ss. 99 and 100 of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00022_192307_1523344595133&sectionId=31774&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00022_192307_1523344595133
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person empowered by this Act to seize and detain`
  line `any ship may, at any reasonable time by day or night, enter any dock-yard, ship-yard or other place`
  line `and make inquiries respecting any ship which he has reason to believe is liable to forfeiture under this`
  line `Act, and may search such ship with a view to ascertaining whether the provisions of this Act have`
  line `been or are being duly observed in respect thereof, and every person in charge of or employed in such`
  line `place shall on request be bound to give the person so empowered all reasonable facilities for such`
  line `entry and search and for making such inquiries.`
  line
  line `(2) The provisions of sections 101, 102 and 103 of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1898 (5 of`
  line `1898)^1`
  line `, shall apply in the case of all searches made under this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (31775)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Courts by which and conditions subject to which offences may be tried.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by the A. O. 1937, for "L.G.".`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00022_192307_1523344595133&sectionId=31775&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00022_192307_1523344595133
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `No Court`
  line `inferior to that of a Presidency Magistrate or Magistrate of the first class shall proceed to the trial of`
  line `any offence punishable under this Act, and no Court shall proceed to the trial of any such offence`
  line `except on complaint made by, or under authority from, the ^1[Central Government].`
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (31776)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title Indemnity.
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00022_192307_1523344595133&sectionId=31776&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00022_192307_1523344595133
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `No prosecution, suit or other legal proceeding shall lie against any person for`
  line `anything in good faith done or intended to be done under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_translations:
  hi obj_root_law_translations_hi
